<h2>6. WEBSOCKET COMMUNICATION PROTOCOL</h2>
<p>To minimize latency, images are sent as <strong>binary WebSocket frames</strong> containing a JPEG compressed buffer directly from the HTML Canvas, bypassing base64 encoding overhead (saves 33% payload size).</p>
<table>
    <tr><th>Message Type</th><th>Direction</th><th>Description</th></tr>
    <tr><td><code>device_paired</code></td><td>Server → Desktop</td><td>Mobile device connected successfully</td></tr>
    <tr><td><code>image_captured</code></td><td>Mobile → Server</td><td>Raw image binary frame sent</td></tr>
    <tr><td><code>capture_progress</code></td><td>Server → Desktop</td><td>Page count update, thumbnails</td></tr>
    <tr><td><code>processing_progress</code></td><td>Server → Both</td><td>Progress percentage + current step</td></tr>
    <tr><td><code>processing_complete</code></td><td>Server → Both</td><td>PDF ready, download URL</td></tr>
</table>

<h2>7. API SPECIFICATION (REST)</h2>
<pre>
SESSION MANAGEMENT
──────────────────
POST   /api/v1/sessions
       → Create new capture session. Returns { session_id, qr_code_url, ws_token }

GET    /capture/{session_id}?token={jwt}
       → Serve the mobile capture UI HTML page

SUBMISSION / PDF
────────────────
GET    /api/v1/submissions/{session_id}/pdf
       → Download the generated PDF

POST   /api/v1/submissions/{session_id}/upload
       → Upload PDF to permanent storage / database

POST   /api/v1/submit-assignment
       → Integration endpoint for parent application
</pre>

<h2>8. DATABASE SCHEMA</h2>
<pre>
TABLE: capture_sessions
───────────────────────
id              UUID PRIMARY KEY
assignment_id   VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL
user_id         VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL
status          ENUM('created', 'paired', 'capturing', 'processing', 'completed')
page_count      INTEGER DEFAULT 0
pdf_path        VARCHAR(500)
created_at      TIMESTAMP WITH TZ

TABLE: captured_pages
─────────────────────
id              UUID PRIMARY KEY
session_id      UUID FK → capture_sessions
page_number     INTEGER NOT NULL
raw_image_path  VARCHAR(500)
has_diagram     BOOLEAN DEFAULT FALSE
</pre>

<h2>9. SECURITY ARCHITECTURE</h2>
<ul>
    <li><strong>Transport Security:</strong> All connections over HTTPS/WSS (TLS 1.3). Nginx handles SSL termination.</li>
    <li><strong>Session Security:</strong> Session IDs are UUID v4. JWT tokens are short-lived (15 minutes), signed with HS256, and passed in the QR code.</li>
    <li><strong>Input Validation:</strong> Max image size of 10MB per frame. Max 50 pages per session. File type validation (JPEG magic bytes check).</li>
    <li><strong>API Security:</strong> API key authentication for integration endpoints. Rate limiting applied (100 requests/min).</li>
    <li><strong>File Storage:</strong> Files stored with UUID names. Auto-cleanup deletes raw images after PDF generation.</li>
</ul>

<h2>10. LATENCY OPTIMIZATION: EAGER VS BATCH</h2>
<p><strong>Recommendation: Use Eager Processing</strong> with Celery chord pattern for minimum perceived latency.</p>
<pre>
EAGER PROCESSING (Low Latency Pattern):
───────────────────────────────────────
Page 1 captured ──▶ [Start processing page 1]
Page 2 captured ──▶ [Start processing page 2] │ Page 1 still running
Page 3 captured ──▶ [Start processing page 3] │ Page 2 still running
User clicks Finish ──▶ [Wait for remaining] ──▶ [Generate PDF]
</pre>

