<h2>13. DEVELOPMENT PHASES & TIMELINE</h2>
<ul>
    <li><strong>Phase 1: Foundation (Week 1-2):</strong> FastAPI setup, Database, Redis, Session API, QR generation.</li>
    <li><strong>Phase 2: Real-time Communication (Week 2-3):</strong> WebSocket manager, Desktop/Mobile handlers, Binary frame protocol.</li>
    <li><strong>Phase 3: Mobile Capture UI (Week 3-4):</strong> Camera access (getUserMedia), Edge detection overlay, Review/Retake flow.</li>
    <li><strong>Phase 4: CV Pipeline (Week 4-6):</strong> Document detection, Shadow removal, Content-aware region classification, Celery integration.</li>
    <li><strong>Phase 5: PDF & Delivery (Week 6-7):</strong> PDF generation, metadata injection, optimization, WS delivery.</li>
    <li><strong>Phase 6: Security & Hardening (Week 7-8):</strong> Rate limiting, CORS, cleanup crons, error handling.</li>
    <li><strong>Phase 7: Testing & Polish (Week 8-10):</strong> Unit/Integration tests, Load testing, latency profiling.</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Total Estimated Timeline: 8-10 weeks (1 developer) or 5-6 weeks (2 developers)</strong></p>

